  "about": {
    "contact_email": "You can contact us via email",
    "description": {
      "title": "Rojava Center for Strategic Studies is an independent, non-profit political and intellectual foundation established based on contemporary historical and strategic necessities.",
      "paragraph1": "Through its work, publications, and writings, it seeks to positively influence the trajectory of historical developments in the political geography of Kurdish societies in general, and Rojava and Syria in particular. This is achieved by presenting and proposing multiple topics, proposals, analyses, studies, surveys, and ideas, organizing international and local seminars, and strategic meetings between political and intellectual elites in the Middle East and the world. The goal is to build a democratic Kurdish and Middle Eastern society based on the values of justice and equality, through the approach of 'democratic nation' that calls for respecting the specificities of all societies, nationalities, religions, and sects, rejecting gender discrimination, respecting women, and calling for full partnership in rights and duties. The center also believes in and works to preserve the environment and human and ecological history by promoting an environmental culture aimed at preserving the civilizational heritage of all human societies.",
      "paragraph2": "Hence, the Rojava Center for Strategic Studies website develops its various follow-ups and research, investing them in formulating strategic future proposals and visions that contribute to raising the level of awareness and critical thinking among individuals and society.",
      "paragraph3": "The site is committed to publishing professional studies, analyses, and journalistic materials, provided their content contributes to reaching and moving towards the truth, away from all forms of oppression, exclusion, and intolerance in all their forms."
    }
  },
